<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-08-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="191" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                        <head>No. 136.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-08-17"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 17,
                                1882</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>McSweeney has been released without conditions. Slatterly was discharged
                            on the 1st of August. The only two remaining cases are those of
                            O’Mahoney and Brophy, and they are being considered by the proper
                            officials.</p>
                        <closer><signed>LOWELL,</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>